'''Mii Shrine''' (みいじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in Hikawa-chō Naoe, {{jalink|Izumo City|Q825166}}, {{jalink|Shimane Prefecture|Q132751}}. It is a shrine associated with traditions concerning Yagami-hime, who appears in the {{jalink|Ōkuninushi myths|Q11433656}}, and her child {{jalink|Konamata-no-Kami|Q11092833}} (this deity), and is worshipped as a god of safe childbirth.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* Konamata-no-Kami (Mii-no-Kami)

He appears in the myths of {{jalink|Ōkuninushi|Q276944|Ōanamuchi-no-Kami}} depicted in the '{{jalink|Kojiki|Q813031}}'. Yagami-hime, who married Ōkuninushi, became pregnant and came as far as {{jalink|Izumo Province|Q582846}}, but fearing the principal wife {{jalink|Suseri-hime|Q8191715|Suseri-bime}}, she pushed the newborn child into the fork of a tree and returned to {{jalink|Inaba Province|Q1054338}}. Because of this, the child was named Konamata-no-Kami.

=== History ===
The shrine is identified with the Mii Shrine listed as an existing government shrine (zaishingi-kan-sha) in the Izumo District entry of the '{{jalink|Izumo no Kuni Fudoki|Q11395858}}', and with the Mii Shrine recorded in the Izumo District of Izumo Province in the '{{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932}}'. Near the shrine grounds, the Sugisawa III site—where nine post holes believed to be the remains of an ancient {{jalink|Taisha-zukuri|Q387874}} shrine building were excavated—has been discovered, and is presumed to have been the original shrine site.

=== Subsidiary and branch shrines ===
* Tenjin Shrine
* Jisson Shrine (じっそんじんじゃ) – an off-site shrine that enshrines the mother deity Yagami-hime

=== Faith ===
Near the shrine are three {{jalink|wells|Q43483}} called “Ikui,” “Sakui,” and “Tsunagai,” and there is a tradition that Yagami-hime used their water for the birth bath at the time of childbirth. It is thought that worship of these three wells originally developed into the shrine.

=== References ===
* Edited by Eiji Shirai and Masanori Toki, *Newly Revised Popular Edition: Encyclopedia of Shrines*, 1997, {{jalink|Tōkyōdō Shuppan|Q11524645}} ISBN 4-490-10474-X
* Kazuhiko Seki, *Annotated Studies on the “Izumo no Kuni Fudoki”*, 2006, {{jalink|Akashi Shoten|Q11512528}} ISBN 4-7503-2376-4
* Yoshiyuki Takinoto, *Dictionary of Ancient Izumo*, 2001, {{jalink|Shin Jinbutsu Ōraisha|Q11501312}} ISBN 4-404-02941-1

